libhybris: strip UBWC-triggering usage bits in HWComposerNativeWindow on aurora

QTI gralloc's IsUBwcEnabled() (hardware/qcom/<soc>/display/gralloc/gr_utils.cpp)
returns true when any of the following bits are set in the buffer usage:

  - GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_COMPOSER       = 0x800        (= BufferUsage::COMPOSER_CLIENT_TARGET)
  - GRALLOC_USAGE_PRIVATE_ALLOC_UBWC    = 0x10000000   (private bit 28; libEGL_adreno
                                                       adds this when creating an EGLSurface)
  - GRALLOC_USAGE_PRIVATE_ALLOC_UBWC_PI = 0x40000000   (private bit 30, "paddingless intra")

When IsUBwcEnabled returns true the allocator stamps the buffer with
DRM_FORMAT_MOD_QCOM_COMPRESSED at AddFB2 time. On aurora (Pixel Watch 2,
Qualcomm Monaco / sw5100), the only SDE SSPP available to SDM for the
launcher's client-composition layer is plane 70 -- a DMA pipe with no UBWC
support -- so atomic-commit returns -EINVAL and the launcher loops in
`prepare: validate failed for display 0: 2`.

HW_FB (0x1000) is NOT a UBWC trigger per gr_utils.cpp; EGL/libui need it for
the buffer to be a valid framebuffer surface. Keep it, add HW_RENDER and
HW_TEXTURE for GPU access, and strip the three UBWC triggers above.

Applied only on aurora via SRC_URI:append:aurora in the libhybris bbappend,
so other watches keep stock behavior bit-for-bit.

Upstream-Status: Pending

Signed-off-by: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>

--- a/egl/platforms/hwcomposer/hwcomposer_window.cpp
+++ b/egl/platforms/hwcomposer/hwcomposer_window.cpp
@@ -128,7 +128,12 @@
     m_width = width;
     m_height = height;
     m_bufFormat = format;
-    m_usage = GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_COMPOSER|GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_FB;
+    // Aurora (Pixel Watch 2 / Monaco): QTI gralloc's IsUBwcEnabled() returns
+    // true when usage has GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_COMPOSER. HW_FB is NOT a UBWC
+    // trigger; it's still needed so EGL/libui consider this a framebuffer
+    // surface. Strip HW_COMPOSER, add HW_RENDER|HW_TEXTURE for GPU access.
+    // Source: hardware/qcom/<soc>/display/gralloc/gr_utils.cpp.
+    m_usage = GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_RENDER|GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_TEXTURE|GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_FB;
     m_bufferCount = 2;
     m_nextBuffer = 0;
 }
@@ -434,7 +439,14 @@
  */
 int HWComposerNativeWindow::setUsage(uint64_t usage)
 {
-    usage |= GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_COMPOSER|GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_FB;
+    // Strip every flag QTI's IsUBwcEnabled() treats as a UBWC trigger:
+    //   - GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_COMPOSER         = 0x800       (= BufferUsage::COMPOSER_CLIENT_TARGET)
+    //   - GRALLOC_USAGE_PRIVATE_ALLOC_UBWC    = 0x10000000  (private bit 28; libEGL_adreno
+    //                                                       sets this on EGLSurface creation)
+    //   - GRALLOC_USAGE_PRIVATE_ALLOC_UBWC_PI = 0x40000000  (private bit 30, "paddingless intra")
+    // Source: hardware/qcom/<soc>/display/gralloc/gr_utils.cpp.
+    usage &= ~(uint64_t)(GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_COMPOSER | 0x10000000ULL | 0x40000000ULL);
+    usage |= GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_RENDER|GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_TEXTURE|GRALLOC_USAGE_HW_FB;
     int need_realloc = (m_usage != usage);
     TRACE("usage=x%" PRIx64 " realloc=%d", usage, need_realloc);
     m_usage = usage;
